prediction.sentence: = Louis, by the grace of God, King of the Franks". 1149, renaissance period).
prediction.region:
840/16 jan. Scezina (-Brunne). Acquisitions of lands from an elder son, by Drogon de Scezina, for his younger son, that he may have an income by which he can reproduce the reputation of his father, a dead knight.

Addition to a charter of Laon establishing the choice for the abbey made by Henry I of France, in which clarification was added dictated by Louis king of France to the effect that the abbey, often destroyed by its warring neighbour, Laon, and not compensating the abbot making the choice in full, was not 'sasûrs l’abbaye à richesses' but 'à bien labeur et travail'.

Source: BEF, I, f. 123r (from St. Pargeaux, p. 124).

841/26 March Forocil, close to Limoges (Haute-Vienne). Confirmation, with their consent accorded in the presence of their kinsmen the counts of Limoges, Albi and la Marche and the nobleman Abbon de Limoges, now, with their consent, bishop of Limoges, and others present of the chosen for the abbots being installed for the abbacy of Limoges. The land thus to be obtained is 1/4 of all texts in the possession of Limoges, as well as all lands from here to Vars and Labaric , resulting from the dispositions at Saix.

Source: BnF, Ms. français 21358 (PO).

842/oct. Drogon de Scezina (-Brunne). The monastery of St. Mary, Bethanie, the bestowal of Douvigny.

Source: J. Guiraud, Les actes de Louis VI publiés par Jules Viard et Paulin Paris, I, vol. III, Paris, 1901, f. cclxv

842/20 nov. Clermont-Ferrand (Cher). Carloman, son of Lothar, giving three kinds of exemption to the monastery of Fleury: from taxes on crossbows, from paying tithes and from revenue payments to episcopal estates.

Source: E Renouard, Recueil des chartes de la Maison de Fleury, Paris, 1858, p. 301

843/later. John of Orleans, bequeathing his goods to the cathedral and Joscelin, canon of Paris, in both their names.

Source: BnF, Ms. français 21357 (ordonnances), f. 31

843/after. A charter of Emeterius, providing that Theutbaldus Secularis, former bishop of Verdun, may put across the title to the church of Blondongescona, succeeded by his brother as abbot.

Source: Pouillé de la province ecclésiastique de Verdun, ed. F. Hauck, tome IV (Narbonnoise, 3), col. 197.

844/before. Nithard, abbot of Noviant (Quatre Vents), confirming various immunities on the part of the monastery of Metz.

Source: Mettensia 13 (1962): 259/275.

844/before. Roger, abbot of Térouanne, confirming certain rights of Bursfeld.

Source: J.-F. Lemarignier, Le pouvoir ducal sous les premiers Capétiens, Paris, 1979, p. 374., nr. 1822.

844/before. A charter of Berengar I with reference to the monastery of St. Anne of Perales and its earliest history.

Source: Triste, necrologia monasterii Sanctae Annae de Perales ad Carriones, in Mittheilungen der Gesellscha

Robin Hood indicting the Sheriff before the Justices: " It is more than two winters since this disheritor promulgated his lists of proscriptions in all parts of the kingdom, and summoned all noble and yeoman to rescue their oppressions And at Nottingham town the king's judge, called the sheriff, and twelve citizens and twelve of his officials to the number of 36, a just number, swore that they would extirpate him and all his company, ravisher and thief, spoiler, fellow and servant. Whether they were more eager to serve the king and this his city, or more needy of money, I know not. We do contend that the plaintiff passed directly through the statute of Mort d'Ancestor, for the dead man had naught but four pence, which the complainants arranged to have divided among them. In addition, Sir Reginald, who is said to be the predecessor of this Robin, should have his dainty France and England, swan and turtle, Easterling and finefoule, salmon and porpoise, falcon and mew, coney and buck, the best rolls on bread. If it seem this to the plaintiff, most simple of minds, he can oversee the ground elder of our patch and the wicker that releases animals underneath the fox's earth. I ask for allowance for the thrice three councils he has been to, and for the excommunication he has twice bought and the pardon he has twice petitioned from the pope. Jeremiah was pardoned once, but three times never, knows thou not that, goody? Now it has been answered twice from Cologny, the mount of mercy, that the said Robin is held by God's pledge with no denier on the bow or arrow of the crossbow, but is of our lawful men in all goods that belong to him for true homage which agreen at Wollaton Woodcock long time past, where he tied this same lead to his grave, in the name of the Trinity, and is free of enmity and felony. Notum facimus universis, tam presentibus quam futuris, quod provi nobis humiliter fuit expositum ex parte amicorum carnalium Hugonis Guiberti, filii Thome Guiberti, quod cum guerris durantibus ecclesia de Bellou in Pictavia per gentes nostras in dictis partibus exisentes, quodem modo fuisset debilitata ne forsita inomici eandem fortificarent. nichilominus Anglici et alii inimici regni nostri de die in diem predictum locum accupare volebant, prout vot et fama laborabant, quod attendenter parrochi dicte ecclesie et alii circonitivi timentes ne forsitam dicti inimici, se ibidem ntiidenere dictusque Hugo ad requestem plurium parrochianorum predictorum, una cum eisdem dictam ecclesiam fortificaverunt causa sue tuicionis, et eandem contra dictos inimicos ben deffenderunt et pro eo pluria victualia et alia bona mobilia in et super paria acceperunt, cumque carissimus primogenitus noster, dux Norman, dum nobis absentibus regnum nostrum regebat pace refor mata inter nos et carissimum fratrem nostrum regem Anglie fecerit generalem abolucionem criminum guerris durantibus commissorum prosecucione civili partibus reservata, dictusque Hugo ad instigacionem suorum emulorum, occasione premissorum posset forsi tam in futurum accusari vel vexari, et propter hoc nobis humiliter supplicarant, ut cum ipse Hugo hactenus fuerit bone fame velimus eidem super hoc nostre misericordie gremium apparire. nos, attentis et consideratis premissis predicto Hugoni facta supradicta ac cetera omnia alia que sub dicta generali abolucione possunt et debent comprehandi, civili prosecucione dutapat partibus reserva ta atque omnem penam corporalem, criminalem et ciivilem, quas erga nos, occasione premissorum potuerit quomodolibet incur risse, remittimus, quittamus ac tenore presencium penitus in dulgemus in casu premisso, ipsumque restituimus ad famam patriam et bona. Dantes, tenore presentium in mandatis senescall Pictavensis ceterisque justiciariis, officiaris nostris aut eorum loca tenentibus, presentibus pariter et futurus, quatinus dictum Hugonem, nostra presenti gracia uti et gaudere pacifice faciant et permittant ipsum in contrarium nullatenus molestantis aut molestari quomodolibet permittentes, sed si quis de bonis suis propter hoc captum seu saisitum extitit eidem volumus restitui indilate, quicquid secus factum vel attemptatum fuerit ad statum pristinum et debitum celeriter reducendo. Quod ut firmum et stabile permaneat in futurum, presentes litteras sigilli nostri mi miine facimus roborari. Salvo in aliis jure nostro et in omnibus quolibet alieno. Actum et Datum Parisius, anno Domini m coclx, mense juiii. Per regem, ad relacionem consilii in quo vos eratis. ferricus.
groundtruth.sentence: nos, attentis et consideratis premissis predicto Hugoni facta supradicta ac cetera omnia alia que sub dicta generali abolucione possunt et debent comprehandi, civili prosecucione dutapat partibus reserva ta atque omnem penam corporalem, criminalem et ciivilem, quas erga nos, occasione premissorum potuerit quomodolibet incur risse, remittimus, quittamus ac tenore presencium penitus in dulgemus in casu premisso, ipsumque restituimus ad famam patriam et bona.
groundtruth.region: Johannes, Dei gratia, Francorum rex. Notum facimus universis, tam presentibus quam futuris, quod, prout nobis humiliter fuit expositum ex parte amicorum carnalium Hugonis Guiberti, filii Thome Guiberti, quod cum guerris durantibus ecclesia de Bellou in Pictavia per gentes nostras in dictis partibus existentes quodam modo fuisset debilitata, ne forsitan inimici eandem fortificarent, nichilominus Anglici et alii inimici regni nostri de die in diem predictum locum occupare volebant, prout vox et fama laborabant, quod attendentes parrochiani dicte ecclesie et alii circonvicini, timentes ne forsitan dicti inimici se ibidem manutenerent, dictus que Hugo, ad requestam plurium parrochianorum predictorum, una cum eisdem dictam ecclesiam fortificaverunt, causa sue tuicionis, et eandem contra dictos inimicos bene deffenderunt et pro eo pluria victualia et alia bona mobilia in et super patria acceperunt ; cum que carissimus primogenitus noster, dux Normannie, dum nobis absentibus regnum nostrum regebat, pace reformata inter nos et carissimum fratrem nostrum regem Anglie, fecerit generalem absolucionem criminum guerris durantibus commissorum, prosecucione civili partibus reservata, dictusque Hugo, ad instigacionem suorum emulorum, occasione premissorum posset forsitam in futurum accusari vel vexari ; et propter hoc nobis humiliter supplicarunt ut, cumipse Hugo hactenus fuerit bone fame, velimus eidem super hoc nostre misericordie gremium apperire. Nos, attentis et consideratis premissis, prediclo litigoni facta supradicta ac cetera omnia alia, que sub dicta generali absolucione possunt et debent comprehandi, civili prosecucione duntaxat partibus reservata, atque omnem penam corporalem, criminalem et civilem, quas erga nos occasione premissorum potuerit quomodolibet incurrisse, remittimus, quittamus ac tenore presencium penitus indulgemus in casu premisso, ipsumque restituimus ad famam, patriam et bona. Dantes tenore presentium in mandatis senescallo Pictavensi ceterisque justiciariis, et officiariis nostris, atit eorum locatenentibus, presentibus pariter et futuris, quatinus dictum Hugonem nostra presenti gratia uti et gaudere pacifice faciant et permittant, ipsum in contrarium nullatenus molestantes aut molestari quomodolibet permitentes, sed si quis de bonis suis propter hoc captum seu saisitum extiterit eidem volumus restitui indilate, quodquid secus factum vel actemptatum fuerit ad statum prestinum et debitum celerint reducendo. Quod ut firmum et stabile permaneat in futurum, presentes litteras sigilli nostri munimine fecimus roborari. Salvo in aliis jure nostro et in omnibus quolibet alieno. Actum et dalum Parisius, anno Domini moccc lxio, mense junii. Per regem, ad relacionem consilii in quo vos eratis. Ferricus.

prediction.region:
840/16 jan. Scezina (-Brunne). Acquisitions of lands from an elder son, by Drogon de Scezina, for his younger son, that he may have an income by which he can reproduce the reputation of his father, a dead knight.

Addition to a charter of Laon establishing the choice for the abbey made by Henry I of France, in which clarification was added dictated by Louis king of France to the effect that the abbey, often destroyed by its warring neighbour, Laon, and not compensating the abbot making the choice in full, was not 'sasûrs l’abbaye à richesses' but 'à bien labeur et travail'.

Source: BEF, I, f. 123r (from St. Pargeaux, p. 124).

841/26 March Forocil, close to Limoges (Haute-Vienne). Confirmation, with their consent accorded in the presence of their kinsmen the counts of Limoges, Albi and la Marche and the nobleman Abbon de Limoges, now, with their consent, bishop of Limoges, and others present of the chosen for the abbots being installed for the abbacy of Limoges. The land thus to be obtained is 1/4 of all texts in the possession of Limoges, as well as all lands from here to Vars and Labaric , resulting from the dispositions at Saix.

Source: BnF, Ms. français 21358 (PO).

842/oct. Drogon de Scezina (-Brunne). The monastery of St. Mary, Bethanie, the bestowal of Douvigny.

Source: J. Guiraud, Les actes de Louis VI publiés par Jules Viard et Paulin Paris, I, vol. III, Paris, 1901, f. cclxv

842/20 nov. Clermont-Ferrand (Cher). Carloman, son of Lothar, giving three kinds of exemption to the monastery of Fleury: from taxes on crossbows, from paying tithes and from revenue payments to episcopal estates.

Source: E Renouard, Recueil des chartes de la Maison de Fleury, Paris, 1858, p. 301

843/later. John of Orleans, bequeathing his goods to the cathedral and Joscelin, canon of Paris, in both their names.

Source: BnF, Ms. français 21357 (ordonnances), f. 31

843/after. A charter of Emeterius, providing that Theutbaldus Secularis, former bishop of Verdun, may put across the title to the church of Blondongescona, succeeded by his brother as abbot.

Source: Pouillé de la province ecclésiastique de Verdun, ed. F. Hauck, tome IV (Narbonnoise, 3), col. 197.

844/before. Nithard, abbot of Noviant (Quatre Vents), confirming various immunities on the part of the monastery of Metz.

Source: Mettensia 13 (1962): 259/275.

844/before. Roger, abbot of Térouanne, confirming certain rights of Bursfeld.

Source: J.-F. Lemarignier, Le pouvoir ducal sous les premiers Capétiens, Paris, 1979, p. 374., nr. 1822.

844/before. A charter of Berengar I with reference to the monastery of St. Anne of Perales and its earliest history.

Source: Triste, necrologia monasterii Sanctae Annae de Perales ad Carriones, in Mittheilungen der Gesellscha

prediction.sentence:
Improvement: The present reading of 1495 restoring absolvere to absolve, is clearly not equivalent to the earlier "relaxare." However, the change from absolve to the composite term avolvereis another reaction to the humanistic culture of the early fifteenth-century courts. In either case, the later reading is superior.

The modern editions, while they do not adequately reflect the multiple efforts of the compiler, at least give a facsimile of the various states of the ms. itself. This new edition is word-for-word identical as far as I can see.

This story is told of Arétin: that the French ambassador seeking to send a letter to the Pope found that the one official at court who would write a personal letter to his Holiness was Arétin, who was not willing to accept

Quod ut firmum et stabile permaneat in futurum, presentes litteras sigilli nostri munimine fecimus roborari. Salvo in aliis jure nostro et in omnibus quolibet alieno. Actum et dalum Parisius, anno Domini moccc lxio, mense junii. Per regem, ad relacionem consilii in quo vos eratis. Ferricus.

ocr.sentence: Salvo in aliis jure nostro et in omnibus quolibet alieno.
ocr.region: Johannes, Dei gratia Francorum rex. Notum facimus universis, tam presentibus quam futuris, quod provi nobis humiliter fuit expositum ex parte amicorum carnalium Hugonis Guiberti, filii Thome Guiberti, quod cum guerris durantibus ecclesia de Bellou in Pictavia per gentes nostras in dictis partibus exisentes, quodem modo fuisset debilitata ne forsita inomici eandem fortificarent. nichilominus Anglici et alii inimici regni nostri de die in diem predictum locum accupare volebant, prout vot et fama laborabant, quod attendenter parrochi dicte ecclesie et alii circonitivi timentes ne forsitam dicti inimici, se ibidem ntiidenere dictusque Hugo ad requestem plurium parrochianorum predictorum, una cum eisdem dictam ecclesiam fortificaverunt causa sue tuicionis, et eandem contra dictos inimicos ben deffenderunt et pro eo pluria victualia et alia bona mobilia in et super paria acceperunt, cumque carissimus primogenitus noster, dux Norman, dum nobis absentibus regnum nostrum regebat pace refor mata inter nos et carissimum fratrem nostrum regem Anglie fecerit generalem abolucionem criminum guerris durantibus commissorum prosecucione civili partibus reservata, dictusque Hugo ad instigacionem suorum emulorum, occasione premissorum posset forsi tam in futurum accusari vel vexari, et propter hoc nobis humiliter supplicarant, ut cum ipse Hugo hactenus fuerit bone fame velimus eidem super hoc nostre misericordie gremium apparire. nos, attentis et consideratis premissis predicto Hugoni facta supradicta ac cetera omnia alia que sub dicta generali abolucione possunt et debent comprehandi, civili prosecucione dutapat partibus reserva ta atque omnem penam corporalem, criminalem et ciivilem, quas erga nos, occasione premissorum potuerit quomodolibet incur risse, remittimus, quittamus ac tenore presencium penitus in dulgemus in casu premisso, ipsumque restituimus ad famam patriam et bona. Dantes, tenore presentium in mandatis senescall Pictavensis ceterisque justiciariis, officiaris nostris aut eorum loca tenentibus, presentibus pariter et futurus, quatinus dictum Hugonem, nostra presenti gracia uti et gaudere pacifice faciant et permittant ipsum in contrarium nullatenus molestantis aut molestari quomodolibet permittentes, sed si quis de bonis suis propter hoc captum seu saisitum extitit eidem volumus restitui indilate, quicquid secus factum vel attemptatum fuerit ad statum pristinum et debitum celeriter reducendo. Quod ut firmum et stabile permaneat in futurum, presentes litteras sigilli nostri mi miine facimus roborari. Salvo in aliis jure nostro et in omnibus quolibet alieno. Actum et Datum Parisius, anno Domini m coclx, mense juiii. Per regem, ad relacionem consilii in quo vos eratis. ferricus.

Nos, attentis et consideratis premissis, prediclo litigoni facta supradicta ac cetera omnia alia, que sub dicta generali absolucione possunt et debent comprehandi, civili prosecucione duntaxat partibus reservata, atque omnem penam corporalem, criminalem et civilem, quas erga nos occasione premissorum potuerit quomodolibet incurrisse, remittimus, quittamus ac tenore presencium penitus indulgemus in casu premisso, ipsumque restituimus ad famam, patriam et bona. Dantes tenore presentium in mandatis senescallo Pictavensi ceterisque justiciariis, et officiariis nostris, atit eorum locatenentibus, presentibus pariter et futuris, quatinus dictum Hugonem nostra presenti gratia uti et gaudere pacifice faciant et permittant, ipsum in contrarium nullatenus molestantes aut molestari quomodolibet permitentes, sed si quis de bonis suis propter hoc captum seu saisitum extiterit eidem volumus restitui indilate, quodquid secus factum vel actemptatum fuerit ad statum prestinum et debitum celerint reducendo. Quod ut firmum et stabile permaneat in futurum, presentes litteras sigilli nostri munimine fecimus roborari. Salvo in aliis jure nostro et in omnibus quolibet alieno. Actum et dalum Parisius, anno Domini moccc lxio, mense junii. Per regem, ad relacionem consilii in quo vos eratis. Ferricus.

prediction.region:
840/16 jan. Scezina (-Brunne). Acquisitions of lands from an elder son, by Drogon de Scezina, for his younger son, that he may have an income by which he can reproduce the reputation of his father, a dead knight.

Addition to a charter of Laon establishing the choice for the abbey made by Henry I of France, in which clarification was added dictated by Louis king of France to the effect that the abbey, often destroyed by its warring neighbour, Laon, and not compensating the abbot making the choice in full, was not 'sasûrs l’abbaye à richesses' but 'à bien labeur et travail'.

Source: BEF, I, f. 123r (from St. Pargeaux, p. 124).

841/26 March Forocil, close to Limoges (Haute-Vienne). Confirmation, with their consent accorded in the presence of their kinsmen the counts of Limoges, Albi and la Marche and the nobleman Abbon de Limoges, now, with their consent, bishop of Limoges, and others present of the chosen for the abbots being installed for the abbacy of Limoges. The land thus to be obtained is 1/4 of all texts in the possession of Limoges, as well as all lands from here to Vars and Labaric , resulting from the dispositions at Saix.

Source: BnF, Ms. français 21358 (PO).

842/oct. Drogon de Scezina (-Brunne). The monastery of St. Mary, Bethanie, the bestowal of Douvigny.

Source: J. Guiraud, Les actes de Louis VI publiés par Jules Viard et Paulin Paris, I, vol. III, Paris, 1901, f. cclxv

842/20 nov. Clermont-Ferrand (Cher). Carloman, son of Lothar, giving three kinds of exemption to the monastery of Fleury: from taxes on crossbows, from paying tithes and from revenue payments to episcopal estates.

Source: E Renouard, Recueil des chartes de la Maison de Fleury, Paris, 1858, p. 301

843/later. John of Orleans, bequeathing his goods to the cathedral and Joscelin, canon of Paris, in both their names.

Source: BnF, Ms. français 21357 (ordonnances), f. 31

843/after. A charter of Emeterius, providing that Theutbaldus Secularis, former bishop of Verdun, may put across the title to the church of Blondongescona, succeeded by his brother as abbot.

Source: Pouillé de la province ecclésiastique de Verdun, ed. F. Hauck, tome IV (Narbonnoise, 3), col. 197.

844/before. Nithard, abbot of Noviant (Quatre Vents), confirming various immunities on the part of the monastery of Metz.

Source: Mettensia 13 (1962): 259/275.

844/before. Roger, abbot of Térouanne, confirming certain rights of Bursfeld.

Source: J.-F. Lemarignier, Le pouvoir ducal sous les premiers Capétiens, Paris, 1979, p. 374., nr. 1822.

844/before. A charter of Berengar I with reference to the monastery of St. Anne of Perales and its earliest history.

Source: Triste, necrologia monasterii Sanctae Annae de Perales ad Carriones, in Mittheilungen der Gesellscha

ocr.region: Johannes, Dei gratia Francorum rex. Notum facimus universis, tam presentibus quam futuris, quod provi nobis humiliter fuit expositum ex parte amicorum carnalium Hugonis Guiberti, filii Thome Guiberti, quod cum guerris durantibus ecclesia de Bellou in Pictavia per gentes nostras in dictis partibus exisentes, quodem modo fuisset debilitata ne forsita inomici eandem fortificarent. nichilominus Anglici et alii inimici regni nostri de die in diem predictum locum accupare volebant, prout vot et fama laborabant, quod attendenter parrochi dicte ecclesie et alii circonitivi timentes ne forsitam dicti inimici, se ibidem ntiidenere dictusque Hugo ad requestem plurium parrochianorum predictorum, una cum eisdem dictam ecclesiam fortificaverunt causa sue tuicionis, et eandem contra dictos inimicos ben deffenderunt et pro eo pluria victualia et alia bona mobilia in et super paria acceperunt, cumque carissimus primogenitus noster, dux Norman, dum nobis absentibus regnum nostrum regebat pace refor mata inter nos et carissimum fratrem nostrum regem Anglie fecerit generalem abolucionem criminum guerris durantibus commissorum prosecucione civili partibus reservata, dictusque Hugo ad instigacionem suorum emulorum, occasione premissorum posset forsi tam in futurum accusari vel vexari, et propter hoc nobis humiliter supplicarant, ut cum ipse Hugo hactenus fuerit bone fame velimus eidem super hoc nostre misericordie gremium apparire. nos, attentis et consideratis premissis predicto Hugoni facta supradicta ac cetera omnia alia que sub dicta generali abolucione possunt et debent comprehandi, civili prosecucione dutapat partibus reserva ta atque omnem penam corporalem, criminalem et ciivilem, quas erga nos, occasione premissorum potuerit quomodolibet incur risse, remittimus, quittamus ac tenore presencium penitus in dulgemus in casu premisso, ipsumque restituimus ad famam patriam et bona. Dantes, tenore presentium in mandatis senescall Pictavensis ceterisque justiciariis, officiaris nostris aut eorum loca tenentibus, presentibus pariter et futurus, quatinus dictum Hugonem, nostra presenti gracia uti et gaudere pacifice faciant et permittant ipsum in contrarium nullatenus molestantis aut molestari quomodolibet permittentes, sed si quis de bonis suis propter hoc captum seu saisitum extitit eidem volumus restitui indilate, quicquid secus factum vel attemptatum fuerit ad statum pristinum et debitum celeriter reducendo. Quod ut firmum et stabile permaneat in futurum, presentes litteras sigilli nostri mi miine facimus roborari. Salvo in aliis jure nostro et in omnibus quolibet alieno. Actum et Datum Parisius, anno Domini m coclx, mense juiii. Per regem, ad relacionem consilii in quo vos eratis. ferricus.

ocr.sentence: le restituant au pays, sa bonne renommée et à ses biens, qui par ban ne seroient confisquez, et imposons silence perpetuel à nostre procureur.
ocr.region: le restituant au pays sa bonne renommée et à ses biens qui par ban ne seroient confisquez et imposons silence perpetuel à nostre procureur. Si donnons en mandement, au gouverneur de la Rochelle, et à touz noz autres justiciers et officiers, et à leurs lieuxtenans, presens et avenir, et à chascun d’eulx, si comme à luy appartendra, que le dit suppliant facent et laissent joir et user paisiblement de nostre presente grace et octroy, et contre la teneur d'icelle ne le molestent traveulerent ou empeschent ou sueffrent, traveller, molester ou empeschier en aucune maniere en corps ou en biens, maiz rapellent et remettent ou facent rapeller et mettre au premier estat et deu tout ce qu'ilz trouvé ront estre ou avoir esté fait au contraire et ses diz biens, se pour ce estoient pris, saisiz, arrestez ou empeschiez l'un mettent et facent mettre sanz delay à plaine delivrance. Et pour ce que ce soit chose ferme et estable à tousjours mais, nous avons fait mettre nostre seel ordenné en absence du grant à ces presentes. Sauf en autres choses nostre droit et l'autruy en toutes. Donné à Paris, l'an de grace m ccciiiix et trois, et de nostre regne le tiers, ou mois de juing. Es requestes de l’ostel. G. Mezon Anneel.
